To achieve the main object, a hydraulic propeller enhancement method comprises the step of:
a) providing a boat and then installing a hydraulic propeller in the boat, wherein the hydraulic propeller comprises a power engine, a water passage, a propeller rotatably accommodated in the water passage and rotatable by the power engine to cause a high-speed axial flow of water, a nozzle located on an outlet of the water passage and terminating in a contracted end piece;
b) installing at least one gas release outlet in the hydraulic propeller at a selected area the high-speed axial flow of water passes;
c) providing a gas guide device comprising at least one guide pipe arranged at a selection location in the boat and connecting a bottom end of the at least one guide pipe to the at least one gas release outlet;
d) employing said hydraulic propeller within said high-speed axial flow of water passing through said at least one gas release outlet, due to Bernoulli's principle, said high-speed axial flow of water enables pressure around said at least one gas release outlet rapidly decreased to form a negative pressure for sucking outside air into a gas inlet located on the top end of said at least one guide pipe during rotation of said propeller ;
e) employing said negative pressure to suck in outside air which is to be guided by said at least one guide pipe into said at least one gas release outlet to mix with water and to produce air bubbles; and
f) subject to compressible gas characteristic, the air bubbles thus produced pass through the contracted end piece of the nozzle are compressed to reduce the size, and the compressed air bubbles expand suddenly subject to a pressure difference between the inside of said contracted end piece and the outside of the nozzle when going out of the nozzle, thereby enhancing the propelling force of the hydraulic propeller.

Referring to FIGS. 3 to 5, a hydraulic propeller enhancement method in accordance with the present invention comprises the steps of:
a) providing a boat 20 in any type or shape, and then installing a hydraulic propeller 30 in the boat 20, wherein the hydraulic propeller 30 comprises a power engine 31, a water passage 33, a propeller 32 rotatably accommodated in the water passage 33 and rotatable by the power engine 31 to cause a high-speed axial flow of water F, as shown in FIGS. 5 and 6, a nozzle 34 located on the-outlet of the water passage 33 and terminating in a contracted end piece 341 and then an outlet 342, and a directional nozzle 35 connected to the outlet 342 of the nozzle 34 (the propeller 30 of the known art, no further detailed description in this regard is necessary);
b) installing at least one gas release outlet 40 in the hydraulic propeller 30 at the water passage 33, the nozzle 34, the directional nozzle 35 or any location where the high-speed axial flow of water F passes, and attaching an axial tube 321 to the propeller 32 to connect an inner end 322 of the axial tube 321 to at least one gas pipe 51 and to have the at least one gas release outlet 40 be formed in each of the aforesaid four components, as shown in FIGS. 5 and 6, or in the outer end 342 of the axial tube 321 where the velocity of the flow of water 141 is high, wherein each gas release outlet 40 can made in, but not limited to, circular shape, and backwardly inclined or perpendicular to the tube wall for causing a suction force of negative pressure upon passing of a high-speed of water;
c) providing a gas guide device 50, which, as shown in FIG. 4, comprises the at least one guide pipe 51 arranged at a selection location in the boat 20 above the water line WL and connected with the bottom end thereof to the at least one gas release outlet 40 at the water passage 33 and/or the nozzle 34 and/or the directional nozzle 35 or the axial tube 321 of the propeller 32 subject to type of the board or actual requirements;
d) employing the hydraulic propeller 30 within the high-speed axial flow of water F passing through the at least one gas release outlet 40, due to Bernoulli's principle, the high-speed axial flow of water F enables pressure around the at least one gas release outlet 40 rapidly decreased to form a negative pressure for sucking outside air into a gas inlet 52 located on the top end of the at least one guide pipe 51 during rotation of the propeller 32 without power consumption to save energy consumption;
e) employing said negative pressure to suck in outside air which is to be guided by said at least one guide pipe 51 into said at least one gas release outlet 40 to mix with water and to produce air bubbles 60; and
f) subject to compressible gas characteristic, the air bubbles 60 are compressed to reduce the size when passing through the contracted end piece 341 of the nozzle 34, and the compressed air bubbles 60 expand suddenly subject to a pressure difference between the inside of the contracted end piece 341 and the outside of the nozzle 34 when they go out of the nozzle 34, enhancing the propelling force of the hydraulic propeller 30.

claim.claim-text:
Verfahren zur Verbesserung eines Wasserstrahlantriebs, das folgenden Schritt umfasst:
a) Bereitstellen eines Boots (20) und anschließend Einbauen eines Wasserstrahlantriebs (30) in dem Boot (20), wobei der Wasserstrahlantrieb (30) eine Kraftmaschine (31), einen Wasserkanal (33), einen drehbar in dem Wasserkanal (33) untergebrachten Propeller (32), der von der Kraftmaschine (31) drehbar ist, um eine axiale Hochgeschwindigkeitswasserströmung (F) zu bewirken, eine an einem Auslass (342) des Wasserkanals (33) befindliche und in einem verengten Endstück (341) endende Düse (34) umfasst;
b) Einbauen von mindestens einem Gasfreisetzungsauslass (40) in dem Wasserstrahlantrieb (30) in einem ausgewählten Bereich, an dem die axiale Hochgeschwindigkeitswasserströmung (F) vorbeiströmt;
c) Bereitstellen einer Gasleitvorrichtung (50), die mindestens ein Leitrohr (51) umfasst, das an einer ausgewählten Stelle in dem Boot (20) angeordnet ist, und Verbinden eines unteren Endes des mindestens einen Leitrohrs (51) mit dem mindestens einen Gasfreisetzungsauslass (40);
d) Verwenden des Wasserstrahlantriebs (30) in der axialen Hochgeschwindigkeitswasserströmung (F), die durch den mindestens einen Gasfreisetzungsauslass (40) strömt, aufgrund des Bernoulli-Prinzips ermöglicht die axiale Hochgeschwindigkeitswasserströmung (F), dass der Druck um den mindestens einen Gasfreisetzungsauslass (40) schnell sinkt, um einen Unterdruck zu erzeugen, um während der Drehung des Propellers (32) Außenluft in einen Gaseinlass (52) einzusaugen, der sich am oberen Ende des mindestens einen Leitrohrs (51) befindet;
e) Verwenden des Unterdrucks zum Einsaugen von Außenluft, die von dem mindestens einen Leitrohr (51) in den mindestens einen Gasfreisetzungsauslass (40) geleitet werden soll, um sich mit Wasser zu vermischen und Luftblasen (60) zu erzeugen; und
f) gemäß der Eigenschaft kompressibler Gase werden die so erzeugten Luftblasen (60), die durch das verengte Endstück (341) der Düse (34) gelangen, komprimiert, um die Größe zu verkleinern, und die komprimierten Luftblasen (60) dehnen sich beeinflusst durch einen Druckunterschied zwischen dem Inneren des verengten Endstücks (341) und dem Äußeren der Düse (34) plötzlich aus, wenn sie die Düse (34) verlassen, wodurch die Antriebskraft des Wasserstrahlantriebs (30) verbessert wird.

A hydraulic propeller enhancement method, comprising the step of:
a) providing a boat (20) and then installing a hydraulic propeller (30) in said boat (20), wherein said hydraulic propeller (30) comprises a power engine (31), a water passage (33), a propeller (32) rotatably accommodated in said water passage (33) and rotatable by said power engine (31) to cause a high-speed axial flow of water (F), a nozzle (34) located on an outlet (342) of said water passage (33) and terminating in a contracted end piece (341);
b) installing at least one gas release outlet (40) in said hydraulic propeller (30) at a selected area said high-speed axial flow of water (F) passes;
c) providing a gas guide device (50) comprising at least one guide pipe (51) arranged at a selected location in said boat (20) and connecting a bottom end of said at least one guide pipe (51) to said at least one gas release outlet (40);
d) employing said hydraulic propeller (30) within said high-speed axial flow of water (F) passing through said at least one gas release outlet (40), due to the Bernoulli's principle, said high-speed axial flow of water (F) enables pressure around said at least one gas release outlet (40) rapidly decreased to form a negative pressure for sucking outside air into a gas inlet (52) located on the top end of said at least one guide pipe (51) during rotation of said propeller (32);
e) employing said negative pressure to suck in outside air which is to be guided by said at least one guide pipe (51) into said at least one gas release outlet (40) to mix with water and to produce air bubbles (60); and
f) subject to compressible gas characteristic, the air bubbles (60) thus produced pass through said contracted end piece (341) of said nozzle (34) are compressed to reduce the size, and the compressed air bubbles (60) expand suddenly subject to a pressure difference between the inside of said contracted end piece (341) and the outside of said nozzle (34) when going out of said nozzle (34), thereby enhancing the propelling force of said hydraulic propeller (30).

Procédé d'amélioration d'hélice hydraulique, comprenant l'étape :
a) de disposition d'un bateau (20), puis d'installation d'une hélice hydraulique (30) dans ledit bateau (20), ladite hélice hydraulique (30) comprenant un moteur (31), un passage d'eau (33), une hélice (32) reçue de manière rotative dans ledit passage d'eau (33) et apte à être entraînée en rotation par ledit moteur (31) pour provoquer un écoulement axial d'eau à grande vitesse (F), une buse (34) située sur une sortie (342) dudit passage d'eau (33) et se terminant dans une pièce d'extrémité rétrécie (341) ;
b) d'installation d'au moins une sortie de libération de gaz (40) dans ladite hélice hydraulique (30) à une zone choisie dans laquelle passe ledit écoulement axial d'eau à grande vitesse (F) ;
c) de disposition d'un dispositif de guidage de gaz (50) comprenant au moins un tuyau de guidage (51) placé à un emplacement choisi dans ledit bateau (20) et reliant une extrémité inférieure dudit au moins un tuyau de guidage (51) à ladite au moins une sortie de libération de gaz (40) ;
d) d'utilisation de ladite hélice hydraulique (30) à l'intérieur dudit écoulement axial d'eau à grande vitesse (F) passant à travers ladite au moins une sortie de libération de gaz (40), en raison du principe de Bernoulli ledit écoulement axial d'eau à grande vitesse (F) permet à la pression autour de ladite au moins une sortie de libération de gaz (40) de diminuer rapidement pour former une pression négative de façon à aspirer de l'air extérieur dans une entrée de gaz (52) située sur l'extrémité supérieure dudit au moins un tuyau de guidage (51) durant la rotation de ladite hélice (32) ;
e) d'utilisation de ladite pression négative pour aspirer de l'air extérieur qui doit être guidé par ledit au moins un tuyau de guidage (51) dans ladite au moins une sortie de libération de gaz (40) pour se mélanger avec de l'eau et produire des bulles d'air (60) ; et
f) en raison de la caractéristique de gaz compressible, les bulles d'air (60) ainsi produites passant à travers la pièce d'extrémité rétrécie (341) de ladite buse (34) sont comprimées pour une réduction de dimension et les bulles d'air comprimées (60) s'étendent soudainement en raison d'une différence de pression entre l'intérieur de ladite pièce d'extrémité rétrécie (341) et l'extérieur de ladite buse (34) lorsqu'elles sortent de ladite buse (34), améliorant ainsi la force de propulsion de ladite hélice hydraulique (30).
